article.headline: Old Dominion 69, Delaware 53
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Isaiah Hunter scored 25 points, and Old Dominion closed out its regular season with a 69-53 victory over Delaware on Saturday. The Monarchs (21-8, 13-5 Colonial Athletic Association) clinched the No. 4 seed in the CAA tournament and will face either Northeastern or James Madison in the quarterfinals March 4. Drew Williamson added 13 points for the Monarchs, and Alex Loughton had nine points and 11 rebounds. The Blue Hens (8-20, 4-14) have lost 20 games in consecutive seasons for the first time in school history. Delaware will be the No. 9 seed for the CAA tournament and will face No. 8 Drexel in the first round on March 3. In his home finale, Harding Nana had 31 points and 18 rebounds -- his 15th double-double of the season and the 39th of his career. Old Dominion never trailed and led 28-15 at halftime, holding Delaware to its lowest first-half point total since the 1992 season. Delaware got within seven after Nana made two free throws with 9:45 remaining. But they would never get any closer as the Monarchs went on a 10-2 run to maintain control.
